100.description: The server has received the request headers, and the client should proceed to send the request body.

101.description: The requester has asked the server to switch protocols.

102.description: The server has received and is processing the request, but no response is available yet.

103.description: Used to return some response headers before final HTTP message.

201.description: The request has been fulfilled and has resulted in a new resource being created.

202.description: The request has been accepted for processing, but the processing has not been completed.

203.description: The server successfully processed the request, but is returning information from another source.

204.description: The server successfully processed the request, but is not returning any content.

205.description: The server successfully processed the request and requires that the requester reset the document view.

206.description: The server is delivering only part of the resource due to a range header sent by the client.

208.description: Used inside a DAV: propstat response element to avoid duplicate enumeration.

226.description: The server has fulfilled a GET request for the resource, and the response is a representation of instance manipulations.

300.description: Indicates multiple options for the resource that the client may follow.

301.description: This and all future requests should be directed to the given URI.

302.description: The resource was found but resides temporarily under a different URI.

303.description: The response to the request can be found under another URI using GET method.

304.description: The resource has not been modified since the last request.

305.description: The requested resource is only available through a proxy.

307.description: The requested resource resides temporarily under a different URI.

308.description: The request and all future requests should be directed to the given URI.

400.description: The server cannot process the request due to a client error.

401.description: Authentication is required and has failed or has not yet been provided.

403.description: The server understands the request but refuses to authorize it.

404.description: The requested resource could not be found.

405.description: A request method is not supported for the requested resource.

406.description: The requested resource cannot generate content acceptable according to Accept headers.

407.description: The client must authenticate with the proxy first.

408.description: The server timed out waiting for the request.

409.description: The request could not be completed due to conflict with the current state of the resource.

410.description: The requested resource is no longer available.

411.description: The request did not specify the length of its content, which is required.

412.description: One or more conditions in request header fields evaluated to false.

413.description: The request is larger than the server is willing to process.

414.description: The URI provided was too long for the server to process.

415.description: The server does not support the media type of the request.

416.description: The client asked for a portion of the file but the server cannot supply it.

417.description: The server cannot meet the requirements of the Expect request-header field.

418.description: Any attempt to instruct a teapot to brew coffee should result in error 418.

421.description: The request was directed at a server that cannot produce a response.

422.description: The request was well-formed but could not be followed due to semantic errors.

423.description: The resource being accessed is locked.

424.description: The request failed due to failure of a previous request.

425.description: Indicates that the server is unwilling to risk processing a request that might be replayed.

426.description: The client should switch to a different protocol.

428.description: The origin server requires the request to be conditional.

429.description: The user has sent too many requests in a given amount of time.

431.description: The server refuses to process the request because headers are too large.

451.description: The user agent requested a resource that cannot legally be provided.

500.description: A generic error message, given when an unexpected condition was encountered.

501.description: The server does not recognize the request method or cannot fulfill it.

502.description: The server was acting as a gateway or proxy and received an invalid response.

503.description: The server is currently unable to handle the request due to overload or maintenance.

504.description: The server did not receive a timely response from an upstream server.

505.description: The server does not support the HTTP protocol version used.

506.description: Transparent content negotiation results in a circular reference.

507.description: The server cannot store the representation needed to complete the request.

508.description: The server detected an infinite loop while processing the request.

510.description: Further extensions to the request are required to fulfill it.

511.description: The client needs to authenticate to gain network access.
